<subSubSection pageNumber="443" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="443">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">Note:</emphasis>
Although some authors have assumed that Linnaeus (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">Sp. Pl.</emphasis>
, ed. 2, 2: 1236. 1763) subsequently transferred 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Conyza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifrons">C. bifrons</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Inula</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, restricting it to the European taxon, it seems clear that this was not the case. On p. 1207 of the same work, Linnaeus also treated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Conyza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifrons">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">C. bifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the same diagnosis as in 1753 but with only the previously cited Plukenet polynomial in synonymy. The Hermann reference was transferred to the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifrons">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">I. bifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, along with three new synonyms. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifrons">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">Inula bifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is evidently a new name in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">Inula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the European plant (albeit with the same epithet), and not a new combination in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">Inula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Conyza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifrons">Conyza bifrons</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
See notes by Godfrey (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="443">J. Elisha Mitchell Sci. Soc.</emphasis>
68: 264. 1952).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
